COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe8
STRING: [Fal] “What is your hometown like, Chris?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfe
STRING: [Chris] “Hmm? Well, it's doing quite well, but it's not
nearly as beautiful as Piova, and still very rural in some
ways.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x144
STRING: [Fal] “I think that's much better than a city that
flourished as a status symbol for the nobility. Although, I
did like the Old District.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x16e
STRING: There wasn't even a hint of a smile in her answer.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x17c
STRING: Lately, Fal hadn't been smiling much.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x188
STRING: Or to put it more accurately, she didn't have to force
any more smiles.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1a0
STRING: She didn't need her near-flawless social skills around
me, at least.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1b6
STRING: I felt genuinely happy about that.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1c4
STRING: Besides, it wasn't like she'd stopped smiling altogether.
She smiled normally whenever she felt happy and
enjoyed herself; the point was it was natural.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1e6
STRING: That was her true self, which only I knew about.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x218
STRING: [Fal] “So, what are we going to do?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x22e
STRING: [Chris] “What to do indeed...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x244
STRING: We had talked about the future many times, but we still
didn't have an answer.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x25a
STRING: That wasn't because we had a lack of options, however.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x280
STRING: Our graduation recital, apparently, had received
extraordinary praise, more than we'd ever expected.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x298
STRING: A few days later, when we went to school for the
ceremony and other events, we found many awards and
offers from orchestras waiting for us.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2ba
STRING: For the moment, our future looked bright.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2c6
STRING: And it seemed that she'd be able to fulfill her dream
someday.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2dc
STRING: Most importantly, no matter which path we chose, we
would never be apart.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x300
STRING: As long as she needed me.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x31a
STRING: As long as she loved me.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x326
STRING: I too was able to pledge my heartfelt love for this girl.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x332
STRING: That's why I was by Fal's side, who wanted to be happy.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x384
STRING: [Fal] “Something on your mind?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x39a
STRING: [Chris] “Yeah. I was thinking about you, Fal.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3cc
STRING: [Fal] “... Weirdo.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3e2
STRING: With that, Fal also turned to look out the window.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x408
STRING: The train had just left the station.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x414
STRING: It hadn't even reached the mountains that encircled the
city of Piova.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x42a
STRING: On the other side of the incredibly long tunnel that ran
through those mountains, it probably wouldn't be
raining.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x442
STRING: It would be my first time seeing blue skies in three
years.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x450
STRING: While imagining that moment, I gave myself up to the
movements of the train and felt the unhurried passage
of time.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x49e
STRING: [Fal] “Ah, we've finally entered the tunnel.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4b4
STRING: [Chris] “Yes, but our destination is about half a day
away.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4d2
STRING: [Fal] “That's far.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4e8
STRING: [Chris] “It sure is.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4fe
STRING: I wondered how far the journey had seemed to me,
back then.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x50a
STRING: Even so, Arietta did come to see me a few times, didn't
she...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x532
STRING: [Fal] “When we come out of this tunnel...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x548
STRING: [Chris] “...Hmm?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x57a
STRING: [Fal] “...Nothing. Still a long way to go, right?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x590
STRING: [Chris] “It's a pretty long tunnel.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5c2
STRING: [Fal] “...Yes.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5d8
STRING: Fal nodded somewhat uncertainly and brought her
hand to her chest.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5ee
STRING: I'd seen that gesture many times before.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5fa
STRING: A kind of habit, perhaps?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x606
STRING: [Chris] “Hey...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x638
STRING: [Fal] “What is it?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x64e
STRING: [Chris] “Is that a habit or something?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x66c
STRING: [Fal] “What do you mean?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x682
STRING: [Chris] “That pendant. You touch it sometimes, with a
pained look. Does it have some special meaning for
you?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6be
STRING: [Fal] “Yes, I do have that habit. As for a special
meaning... Yes, I guess it is special to me.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6de
STRING: [Chris] “Something important?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x710
STRING: [Fal] “Yes... You could say that. This is... The only thing I
have from the beginning.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x730
STRING: [Chris] “...The only thing?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x762
STRING: [Fal] “Apparently, when I was left at the shelter, this
pendant was the only thing on me. A silver pendant and
a dirty towel. Nothing else, not even a name.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x78c
STRING: [Chris] “...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7aa
STRING: [Fal] “It's made to look like a pair of wings, this pendant.
Perhaps the person who'd left it with me wanted me to
fly high.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7d4
STRING: She didn't have the notion of parents.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7e0
STRING: During her childhood in the shelter, Fal only had herself,
the people running the shelter, and children in similar
circumstances around her.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7f6
STRING: It didn't seem like she found it upsetting, but she'd said
many times before that she was never going back to
that place.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x80c
STRING: When she went there at the start of the year, it had
been at the instruction of the nobleman who adopted
her, to improve her impression of it.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x83e
STRING: [Fal] “Of course, there's no way of ever knowing the
truth.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x854
STRING: Fal touched the pendant once again, a self-deprecating
smile on her lips.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x86a
STRING: Because she'd touched it so many times, perhaps, that
pair of dull grey wings were so grimy, it was hard to
imagine its original color.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8a6
STRING: [Fal] “But these slightly tarnished wings kinda suit you,
they're beautiful, even.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8bc
STRING: [Chris] “Huh?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8da
STRING: [Fal] “Asino once said that to me. Although it's gotten
dirtier since then because I keep touching it. I heard it
used to be bright silver.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x904
STRING: [Chris] “...I see.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x936
STRING: [Fal] “But it's just some cheap trinket, so it became this
color very quickly. The chain broke too, and now it
hangs on a leather cord.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x960
STRING: She sounded unimpressed, but she was still toying with
it, with a kind of fondness.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x976
STRING: [Chris] “...It's pretty.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9a8
STRING: [Fal] “...Hmm?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9be
STRING: [Chris] “The wings, and you too, Fal.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9f0
STRING: [Fal] “...Moron.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa06
STRING: With that, she finally let go of the wings.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa2e
STRING: [Fal] “Did you talk to Asino after that?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa44
STRING: [Chris] “Only briefly. But he wasn't angry at me, and
despite his fears, I had never been angry at him, either.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa76
STRING: [Fal] “So you guys made up?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa8c
STRING: [Chris] “...On the surface, yes.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xaaa
STRING: [Fal] “Great.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xac0
STRING: It irked me a little to hear her, the cause of that episode,
speak so casually.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xad6
STRING: But that was the kind of person she was, and I'd
accepted that fact.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xae2
STRING: [Chris] “But nothing was said about you, Fal. I doubt he
would've been able to forgive you.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb1e
STRING: [Fal] “I don't mind. I deserve it, after all. If hating me
makes him feel better, then that's what he should do.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb48
STRING: [Chris] “Isn't it your loss to be hated by others?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb7a
STRING: [Fal] “Not if someone worthy of that hatred is by my
side.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb90
STRING: Such comments no longer made my heart race.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb9c
STRING: But I knew that was the truth, so I let it slide.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xbdc
STRING: Suddenly, the train car was filled with light.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xbe8
STRING: It was so blinding, I almost had to shut my eyes.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xbfe
STRING: But even so, I couldn't take my eyes off the view outside
the window.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc14
STRING: [Chris] “Ah... The sky, it's blue.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc32
STRING: [Fal] “...Yes.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc48
STRING: [Chris] “Ha... Ha-ha. It's been three years.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc66
STRING: [Fal] “...Indeed.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc8c
STRING: [Chris] “We'll be here for a while longer, but I feel a little
better now.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcbe
STRING: [Fal] “Great.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcd4
STRING: [Chris] “What about you, Fal? Aren't you moved?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcf2
STRING: [Fal] “...I was just on this train, earlier this year.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd08
STRING: [Chris] “Ah... That's right. But for me, it's been a really
long time.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd26
STRING: [Fal] “I know.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd3c
STRING: Fal kept looking out the window, showing no interest in
my reactions.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd48
STRING: I'd acted all excited, just like a little kid, and I felt a little
embarrassed.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd5e
STRING: [Chris] “...Sorry.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd88
STRING: Fal laughed, finally, and shook her head as if to say it
didn't matter.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd9e
STRING: Then she suddenly said something I hadn't even
thought about.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdbc
STRING: [Fal] “Hey, Chris?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdd2
STRING: [Chris] “...What?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdf0
STRING: [Fal] “When we get there, are you going to see Arietta?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe06
STRING: [Chris] “...What for?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe38
STRING: [Fal] “I think you need to talk to her.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe4e
STRING: [Chris] “Like I said... What for?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe80
STRING: [Fal] “If you don't, we probably can't go any further.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe96
STRING: [Chris] “...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xec8
STRING: [Fal] “I've been thinking about it all along. You still care
about Arietta, Chris.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xee8
STRING: [Chris] “...I don't deny that. But I'm with you now, Fal,
and-”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf10
STRING: [Fal] “I know, but...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf42
STRING: [Fal] “I want to start my life with you after everything
has been settled, or is that too much to ask?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf62
STRING: [Chris] “...No.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf80
STRING: [Fal] “Then, you'll do it?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf96
STRING: [Chris] “...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfac
STRING: I swore I would do whatever I could for her.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfb8
STRING: And so I...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfc4
STRING: [Chris] “Alright.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfda
STRING: I gave my word.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1002
STRING: [Fal] “...Chris, I'm sorry.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1018
STRING: [Chris] “Why are you apologizing? It's okay. If that's
what you want, Fal, I'll do it.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1054
STRING: [Fal] “...Okay. And in return...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x106a
STRING: Fal slowly took off the necklace and broke the wings
into two pieces.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1080
STRING: She gave me one of them.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x10c8
STRING: [Fal] “These are my wings. With them, I'll fly high.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x10e6
STRING: [Fal] “And this wing, Chris, I'm placing in your care. I
can't fly with just one, but the two of us can go
wherever we want to.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1106
STRING: [Chris] “...Thanks.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x112c
STRING: I took it and squeezed it gently.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1138
STRING: The wing was a little dirty, but it definitely hadn't lost its
beauty.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x114e
STRING: Holding the wing with which I'd support her, I tried to
imagine our future together.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x116c
STRING: [Fal] “Will you stay by my side, always?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1182
STRING: [Chris] “Of course.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x11a0
STRING: [Fal] “I will stay by your side too.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x11be
STRING: [Fal] “...Forever.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1236
STRING: We were back in the city of rain.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1242
STRING: Over and over again, the sound of my Fortelle was
offered up in her service.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1278
STRING: I sensed her standing behind me, I heard her voice next
to my ear.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1284
STRING: That was the constant scene in the room which we
shared.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x12a2
STRING: [Fal] “Chris. I will stay by your side forever.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x12ce
STRING: The tarnished wings made a dull sound when they
knocked against each other.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x12e8
STRING: Where would we go on these wings?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1302
STRING: Where could we go?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x130e
STRING: Almost immediately, the sound was erased by the
Fortelle.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x131c
STRING: And then, her voice was laid over it all.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x132a
STRING: I focused on the keyboard, pouring all of my rising
emotions into the music.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1342
STRING: Even after her song ended, she did not move.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1368
STRING: [Fal] “I love you, Chris. You, and the sound of your
Fortelle.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1390
STRING: [Fal] “I'll stay by your side, forever.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x13a6
STRING: Whispering this in my ear, Fal gave a satisfied smile.
